Added:  This adds a new interpolate_field_on_particles_fast
function which uses the FePointEvaluator class to interpolate fields on particles. 
This does not replace the old interpolate_field_on_particles because the 
new function requires knowing the number of components at compile time
whereas the regular one does not. The fast version can also use a mapping
whereas the regular one inherently assumes a mappingQ1. 
